The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and cycles/paths in graphs, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of graph connectivity (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT), as well as computational complexity (cs.CC) in terms of NP-completeness.
